## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

**10 tests, 0 meaningful verifications.** This is a textbook **coverage-touching** suite — every public method on `ProductCatalog` is called in declaration order, but almost nothing is actually asserted. These tests will report ~95% line coverage while catching zero regressions.

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| Critical | 7 |
| High | 1 |
| Medium | 2 |
| Low | 0 |

---

### Critical Findings

#### 1. Coverage Touching (Systemic — entire test class)

The suite methodically calls every public method on `ProductCatalog` with no or trivial assertions. This is the root cause of "95% coverage, bugs in prod."

**Tests with zero assertions (4 of 10):**

| Test | Line | What it misses |
|------|------|----------------|
| `AddProduct_Works` | 17–21 | Never verifies the product was actually stored |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` | 31–36 | Never verifies the price changed |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` | 38–43 | Never verifies the product was removed |
| `GetProductCount_Works` | 62–66 | Never checks the returned count |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` | 68–74 | Never checks discounted prices |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` | 84–88 | Never verifies products were imported |

**Fix — example for `AddProduct`:**
```csharp
// BEFORE (line 17-21): proves nothing
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_Works()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);
}

// AFTER: verifies the product is retrievable with correct values
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_ProductIsRetrievableBySkuWithCorrectValues()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);

    _catalog.AddProduct(product);

    var stored = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual("Widget", stored?.Name);
    Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, stored?.Price);
}
```

**Fix — `UpdatePrice`:**
```csharp
// AFTER
[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_ExistingProduct_PriceIsUpdated()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));

    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);

    var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated?.Price);
}
```

**Fix — `RemoveProduct`:**
```csharp
// AFTER
[TestMethod]
public void RemoveProduct_ExistingProduct_ProductIsNoLongerRetrievable()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));

    _catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");

    Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
